===Noun===
'''hoser'''
#{{slang}} (''Canadian'') A person whose self interest often outweighs any ethical considerations. Not overtly criminal but know to participate in petty infractions and rule bending. Example: A hoser would consume food or alcoholic beverages, typically pizza and beer, with complete disregard to ownership or sharing. Derivation: From the use of a hose to syphon gasoline from automobile gas tanks.